
#PING 

Ping Stands For Packet Internet Groper.
Ping is a Function That Uses ICMP Protocol,
Ping Is Used In Networking To Check The Reachability or Connectivity.

Ex - Ping 192.168.0.1

It Means Device Sends An ICMP (Internet Contro Message Protocol) Echo Message To The Destination For Which, We Are Trying To Check The Reachability.
If an ICMP Echo Reply Comes Back Then Devices Knows That There Is Bi-Directional Reachability.
